# Cursor Governance — Update Rules & Skills with Feature Changes

Whenever you implement a feature, fix a production bug, or introduce a new pattern, you MUST also update the relevant AI guidance files so future work stays consistent.

## When to update guidance

Update `.cursor/rules/`, `.cursor/skills/`, and/or `.cursor/agents/` when you:

- Add a new user-facing module, page, or rename UI terminology (e.g. “Flows” → “Integration”).
- Add/extend backend entities, trigger events, or action types.
- Change API request/response shapes or validation rules.
- Add new cross-cutting behaviors (auth/session timeout handling, error boundaries, runtime constraints).
- Add non-trivial UI behaviors that should be consistent elsewhere (keyboard delete, default viewport behavior).

## What “updated” means

- Document the new behavior and file locations.
- Add/adjust globs so rules apply to the right files.
- Call out critical constraints (e.g. Slack Incoming Webhooks require `{ text }` payloads).
- Keep changes minimal and high-signal; avoid duplicating existing rules.

## Completion check

Before finishing any feature PR, verify:

- New or changed behavior is reflected in at least one rule/skill/agent doc.
- Existing rules/skills/agents that mention old behavior are updated.

